column5: Just got back from a couple hours on cooks bay for pike, managed a solid 30 incher and a very nice 35 incher that fought harder then the 41 I caught a couple weeks back.  I've been reading all these posts about people being 's on the water, I had one this evening as well, had the whole lake and he chose too speed past me at about 25 feet. Damn good thing I wasn't in a 12 foot tinny.
Nice one. Whats the water temps now?
Not sure, don't have a thermometer on the boat
nice fish man... those people are as-tol lolz In time they will get what they deserve...  ha ha
nice looking pike! sure wish my cottage lake could produce pike like that rather than 22 inch snotrockets
nice ! we got a couple 28 inchers last night also and 1 3lb smallie !
Right on man.  I've yet to catch a Simcoe pike.  I'll have to go spend a morning down there one day this summer.  What depth where you targeting?
They are in about 18-20 fow right now
....ya, guess I shouldn't complain about the snotrockets
